12 (b) The governor shall appoint co-chairs for the task
13 force.
14
15 (c) The task force shall:
16
17 (i) Conduct a comprehensive analysis of the
18 sources of revenues currently available to local
19 governments, school districts and special districts as
20 designated in the Wyoming Constitution and Wyoming
21 statutes;
22
3 HB0320

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0788
1 (ii) Determine whether the revenues analyzed in
2 paragraph (i) of this subsection can provide for the
3 services provided by local governments, school districts
4 and special districts, and meet the constitutional mandate
5 for an equal and adequate education of all Wyoming children
6 while ensuring equal and uniform taxation within all
7 classes and subclasses of property;
8
9 (iii) Develop recommendations for providing
10 sustainable revenues for local governments, special
11 districts and schools through 2050 that take into account
12 all forecasted costs, potential revenues and declines in
13 revenues at the state and local levels through 2050;
14
15 (iv) Report its findings and recommendations,
16 including any recommended legislation, to the governor, the
17 Management Council and the Joint Revenue Interim Committee
18 not later than December 31, 2026.
19
20 (d) The task force shall be staffed by the Wyoming
21 department of revenue with assistance from the legislative
22 service office.
23
4 HB0320

