1 (e) Subject to available funding, the task force may
2 recommend to the governor retention of consultants as
3 necessary to fulfill its duties under this section. State
4 agencies shall provide information to the task force as
5 requested by the task force.
6
7 (f) The legislative members of the task force shall
8 receive salary, per diem and travel expenses in the manner
9 and amount prescribed by W.S. 28-5-101. Task force members
10 representing Wyoming state government or its subdivisions
11 shall be considered to be acting within the scope of
12 regular employment when conducting the official business of
13 the task force and shall receive their regular pay without
14 additional compensation, except that those members
15 shall receive mileage and per diem as provided for other
16 members of the task force under this subsection if the
17 members are not reimbursed by their employer. All other
18 members of the task force shall not receive salary but
19 shall receive per diem and mileage in the amount provided
20 for members of the legislature under W.S. 28-5-101 when
21 conducting the official business of the task force.
